    "notes": "High-fidelity detection signals: (1) executable running from C:\\ProgramData\\ in a non-vendor-namespaced subdirectory (WindowsUpdate vs Microsoft\\...) spawned by a user-context mail client (OUTLOOK.EXE) — parent-child pair is anomalous; (2) binary has no Authenticode signature (not modeled in ECS but should be checked via process.code_signature.trusted); (3) near-immediate outbound TLS to a non-Microsoft IP within seconds of first execution; (4) benign equivalents share ProgramData path prefix and same user but exhibit trusted parent chains (services.exe, svchost Schedule) and versioned/vendor-namespaced install paths. Tune by adding code_signature.trusted:false and excluding known-good parent processes (services.exe, msiexec.exe, svchost.exe -k netsvcs)."
  },
